review_comments:
['`_waitForCommittedSession` now races `onDidCommitSession` against `responseCompletePromise` and rejects immediately when the response completes first. However, `IChatSessionsService.onDidCommitSession` is documented as firing *after the first turn completes* (src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/common/chatSessionsService.ts:334-338), which can coincide with (or be scheduled after) `responseCompletePromise` resolution. This can cause false failures in normal flows where the session commits right after the response completes (leading to unnecessary errors/log noise and temp-session cleanup).

Consider changing this to start a short grace/timeout *after* `responseCompletePromise` resolves (e.g. wait for commit for N ms), and only then reject/cleanup if commit still hasn’t happened. Also consider throwing a cancellation-typed error when this path is triggered by user stop/cancel, so callers don’t treat it as an unexpected failure.
```suggestion
				const commitAfterResponseGracePeriodMs = 2_000;

				// The commit event is documented to fire after the first turn
				// completes, so it can be scheduled at about the same time as, or
				// just after, response completion. Wait briefly after the response
				// completes before treating the missing commit as a failure.
				const committedBeforeResponse = await Promise.race([
					commitPromise.then(uri => ({ committed: true as const, uri })),
					responseCompletePromise.then(() => ({ committed: false as const })),
				]);

				if (committedBeforeResponse.committed) {
					return committedBeforeResponse.uri;
				}

				const committedAfterResponse = await raceTimeout(commitPromise, commitAfterResponseGracePeriodMs);
				if (committedAfterResponse) {
					return committedAfterResponse;
				}
```', '`_cleanupTempSession` removes the temp chat from `_sessionCache` and fires a removed event, but it doesn’t clear related multi-chat state. In multi-chat mode, `_chatToSession` caches `ISession` wrappers in `_sessionGroupCache`, and other cleanup paths delete `_sessionGroupCache` entries (e.g. send-first-chat error handling around 1418). Leaving the cached wrapper behind can leak memory and may leave stale group/session bookkeeping.

Consider deleting `_sessionGroupCache` for the affected session/group id, and removing any corresponding entries from `_groupModel` when present (e.g. `removeChat`/`deleteSession` if the temp id was ever added).
```suggestion
		const removedSession = this._chatToSession(chatSession);
		const key = chatSession.resource.toString();
		this._sessionCache.delete(key);
		this._sessionGroupCache.delete(chatSession.id);
		if (removedSession.id !== chatSession.id) {
			this._sessionGroupCache.delete(removedSession.id);
		}

		const groupModel = this._groupModel as SessionsGroupModel & {
			removeChat?(chatId: string): void;
			deleteSession?(sessionId: string): void;
		};
		groupModel.removeChat?.(removedSession.id);
		groupModel.deleteSession?.(removedSession.id);

		if (this._currentNewSession?.id === chatSession.id) {
			this._currentNewSession = undefined;
		}
		this._onDidChangeSessions.fire({ added: [], removed: [removedSession], changed: [] });
```', 'The new temp-session cleanup behavior (archive/delete falling back to `_cleanupTempSession`, plus bounded waits in `_waitForCommittedSession`/`_waitForSessionInCache`) isn’t covered by existing unit tests in this area. There are provider tests (src/vs/sessions/contrib/copilotChatSessions/test/browser/copilotChatSessionsProvider.test.ts), but none assert that stopping/cancelling before commit removes the session from the list or that archive/delete works for an uncommitted temp session.

Please add tests that simulate an uncommitted temp session and verify it is removed on delete/archive, and (ideally) a cancellation path where commit never fires so the bounded wait cleans up without leaving a stuck entry.', 'Fixed', 'Added', 'Fixed', "Ok I know your PR didn't add this (https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/pull/305880) but I do not like seeing  committed sessions and untitled sessions. Tyler and I have been trying  to clean this up and were making real progress. I will follow up because it's disappointing that this debt is now in the new sessions code too", 'Please always use `isEqual` for uri comparisons', 'And also not this commit but these should be `ResourceMap`. It saves a lot of potential pain', "I agree, I think this came with the re-do of the sessions list and switching to sessions providers that register harnesses that @sandy081 did.
I'm not super comfortable with changing it without the help of Sandeep so I will defer that to him ", 'Changed it ', '## Pull request overview

Fixes a Sessions-window edge case where stopping a session before it commits (untitled → real URI swap) leaves a “Working…” entry stuck in the session list and makes archive/delete silently no-op. The change is focused in the Copilot chat sessions provider under `vs/sessions`.

**Changes:**
- Bound the “wait for commit” and “wait for cache population” helpers with response completion and safety timeouts, disposing listeners on all paths.
- Enabled archive/delete to clean up uncommitted temp sessions directly from the provider cache.
- Added a dedicated `_cleanupTempSession` helper to centralize removal and event firing for temp sessions.



']

