review_comments:
["`getSummary(full = this._needsFullSnapshot)` no longer uses `full` to control snapshot detail: it always calls `page.ariaSnapshot(...)`. This changes the semantics of the `full` flag (and makes `_needsFullSnapshot` largely ineffective) and can be a performance regression for call sites that previously requested incremental summaries by passing `full=false`.

Consider either (a) removing the `full`/`_needsFullSnapshot` concept entirely now that incremental snapshots aren’t available, or (b) using `full` to gate whether an aria snapshot is collected (e.g. only include it when `full===true`, otherwise return just URL/dialog/logs) and updating call sites accordingly.

See below for a potential fix:
```
		let snapshot = '';
		if (full) {
			const snapshotFromPage = await this.safeRunAgainstPage((page) => page.ariaSnapshot({ mode: 'ai' })).catch(() => {
				this._needsFullSnapshot = true;
				return undefined;
			});
			snapshot = snapshotFromPage?.trim() ?? '';
		}

		const title = await this.safeRunAgainstPage((page) => page.title()).catch(() => '');

		const logs = this._logs;
		this._logs = [];
```", "Nit: can we make this `Parameters<playwright.Page['ariaSnapshot']>[0] & { _track?: string }`", "## Pull request overview

Upgrades the integrated browser’s Playwright dependency to v1.59.1 and updates the page summarization implementation to use the newer public Playwright API for AI-oriented accessibility snapshots.

**Changes:**
- Bump `playwright-core` to `1.59.1` and `@playwright/test` to `^1.59.1`.
- Replace usage of the hidden `_snapshotForAI(...)` API (and its local type augmentation) with `page.ariaSnapshot({ mode: 'ai' })`.
- Simplify summary snapshot handling to treat the returned snapshot as a single trimmed string.

### Reviewed changes

